# Railway is configured per service with Root Directory = /backend, so it
# only uploads the backend/ subtree. Frontend / sdk / docs etc. are outside
# that root and never reach Railway. Patterns below focus on what's inside
# backend/ and apply during the upload phase.

# Heavy outputs
**/target/
**/node_modules/
**/mutants.out/
**/mutants.out.old/

# Local secrets — never push
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Local dev scratch
*.proof
*.wtns
test-ledger/
.anchor/
.surfpool/
.yarn/
**/tests/fixtures/

# VCS metadata
.git/

# Note: backend/artefacts/zksettle_slice.{json,ccs,pk} ship as part of the
# normal upload — no whitelist needed since nothing above excludes them.
